(2, '<h1>Could Smart Parking Solutions Help to Reduce Pollution</h1>\r\n', 'assets/uploads/Could_Smart_Parking_Solutions_Help_to_Reduce_Pollution.jpg', '<p>Smart parking systems collect data in real time and provide users with a better understanding of the amount of parking spaces available around them.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>India appears to be on the right road toward a better parking policy. According to speculations, Indian administration may soon enable car registration only when the vehicle owner shows a certification confirming parking space availability. During the registration process, this certification must be shown to the authorities. This measure will assist the government in overcoming the country&#39;s traffic and space congestion issues, particularly in cities.</p>\r\n', '<p>Smart parking systems collect data in real time and provide users with a better understanding of the amount of parking spaces available around them.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p>India appears to be on the right road toward a better parking policy. According to speculations, Indian administration may soon enable car registration only when the vehicle owner shows a certification confirming parking space availability. During the registration process, this certification must be shown to the authorities. This measure will assist the government in overcoming the country&#39;s traffic and space congestion issues, particularly in cities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Consider all of the unnecessary gas, petroleum, oil, etc. that these automobiles consume on their 10-15 minute long hunt for parking — every single day. It is well known that automobiles release more toxic emissions when their engines are turned on when stalled in traffic than when they are travelling at greater speeds. It&#39;s no wonder, therefore, that India&#39;s air pollution levels have been steadily growing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p>For a long time, India&#39;s major cities - Delhi, Mumbai, Bangalore, and others – have s