behavior and parking violations. Furthermore, if there was less spot-searching traffic on the roads, accidents caused by the obstruction of hunting for parking may be reduced.</li>\r\n <li>Safety and Security of the Space: Users can only utilize our parking places for registered cars, and our spot representative will be on hand to recognize any suspicious conduct or parking offences.</li>\r\n <li>Real-time data and trend insight: Over time, a digital parking system may collect data that indicates patterns and linkages between parking lots and users. These trends might be quite useful to parking lot owners when it comes to determining how to respond to vehicles. Booking confirmation, start time reminder, end time reminder, payment notice, and so on are all sent in real time, especially when dealing with ‘ParkingAdda&#39;.</li>\r\n <li>New Revenue Streams include: Individuals, organizations, and other institutions can generate a passive income by renting out their premises.</li>\r\n <li>Easy Integrated Payments: The &#39;ParkingAdda&#39; application collects and distributes invoicing and payments. This might also help the organization maintain account transparency between consumers and vendors.</li>\r\n <li>Increased Employment Costs: Several additional revenue sources are potential with this smart parking system. For example, we would have parking lot representatives, which would increase employment in India during these times of job scarcity.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p>As evidence of the aforementioned advantages, any organization or government would surely profit from the usage of a digital parking solution such as the &#39;ParkingAdda&#39; online Digital Parking app. Individuals are still unable to locate a parking space in some of the world&#39;s major cities, where there are around four parking places per car. As the world&#39;s population expands and gets more sophisticated, it&#39;s more important than ever to put in place a user-friendly and well-planned parking system that can be used anywhere. In India, a ParkingAdda is a need-based solution for the benefit of all citizens as well as the environment as a whole.</p>\r\n', 1, '19-10-22', '', 'parking'),
(3, '<h1><strong>Did you know that a Delhi commuter spends more than 80 hours a year</strong></h1>\r\n', 'assets/uploads/Did_you_know_that_a_Delhi_commuter_spends_more_than_80_hours_a_year.jpg', '<p>The issue is straightforward: even as the number of automobiles has increased, parking space in Indian cities has stayed steady or decreased to serve the need of the growing population. Rising parking demand places enormous strain on land, especially when it is restricted and expensive, as it is in metropolises. For Example: in New York&#39;s midtown district, the average road area per person is 33.3 square meters, yet in Mumbai&#39;s Null Bazaar, it is barely more than 1.7 square meters. This means that maintaining a car in Mumbai is roughly 20 times more expensive\\difficult than one in New York.</p>\r\n', '<p>The issue is straightforward: even as the number of automobiles has increased, parking space in Indian cities has stayed steady or decreased to serve the need of the growing population. Rising parking demand places enormous strain on land, especially when it is restricted and expensive, as it is in metropolises. For Example: in New York&#39;s midtown district, the average road area per person is 33.3 square meters, yet in Mumbai&#39;s Null Bazaar, it is barely more than 1.7 square meters. This means that maintaining a car in Mumbai is roughly 20 times more expensive\\difficult than one in New York.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Indian metropolises are facing a mobility dilemma as a result of fast economic and demographic expansion. Today&#39;s cities experience enormous strain or pressure on parking spots, resulting in challenges such as traffic congestion, unequal demand and supply, and environmental dangers, to mention a few. India suffers from chaotic conditions such as packed pathways, illegal parking, two – side parking, and criminal activities owing to inadequate monitoring as a result of bad parking management and legislation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Let&#39;s take a look at some of the most critical parking challenges surrounding Indian cities today.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Overcrowded Parking lots</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>One of the most prevalent issues nowadays is a lack of parking places. Vehicles continue to outnumber available parking places, choking streets. Incidences of violence owing to overcrowding, distorted automobiles due to a lack of space, and overcharging for parking are some of the problems that arise as a consequence. To address the issue, most localities suggest adding parking spots. Despite limited land space and resources, parks and abandoned plots are being exploited as possible parking spots, and multi-level facilities are being created.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Tariffs that are unregulated</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Parking spots are in short supply due to an uncontrolled price system. Parking in Indian metropolises is either free or modestly charged, with costs remaining uncontrolled for many years. For example, Mumbai charges the same parking cost that it did years ago and has one of the world&#39;s lowest fares. Because parking prices cease to rise after a set amount of time, the longer a person remains in a parking place, the less they must pay. For Example:  Parking is at Rs. 20 per hour in Sarojini Nagar, Delhi, with a typical cost of Rs. 100 for 24 hours (Figures taken are approx.), making parking much more affordable.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>On-Street Parking vs. Off-Street Parking</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Another issue in Indian cities is the lopsided demand for on-street parking, which is less expensive than off-street parking. On-street parking difficulties can create delays, especially on busy roadways. Tariff balance is required for both types of areas to be properly utilized. For example, San Francisco has tried and adjusted hourly fees according to the demand and provided off-peak discounts to reduce congestion around garages during rush hour. ParkingAdda has developed their very own Made in India technology, to simply and increase authorized parking options. They provide easy online parking options along with better vehicle safety provisions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>                                                                              </p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Cruising</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Another issue that emerges as a result of a scarcity of parking places in Indian cities is cruising, which involves automobiles hunting for a parking spot, resulting in long lines, congestion, and pollution. When there is no free on-street parking, most cars opt to cruise rather than pay for parking. Indian metros offer an economic incentive to cruise by underpricing on-street parking. Once occupied, low-cost parking is not abandoned for hours, and cases of automobiles being left for days have been documented. Booking online through apps like ‘ParkingAdda’ reduces cruising to around 90 % as they offer booking spots up to 36 hours in advance, MAP guide to the exact spot as well as they have a verifier or representative at every spot who you can call for any further assistance.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Parking in residential neighborhoods</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Parking spots are nearly often built into residential units in Indian metros since it is believed that designs without them will not attract purchasers. This raises the entire cost of development, which is exacerbated when parking spots are left empty. Because parking construction costs the same whether the structure is a luxury high-rise or a basic apartment complex, lower-income inhabitants, who are less likely to own automobiles, end up bearing the burden of parking expenditures, effectively subsidizing parking for others. Any such burdens of can be rented out to Parking Adda, who will turn these expenditures into huge incomes for the buildings or societies. Residents are frequently subjected to spillover parking as a result of commercial visits and excessive car traffic.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Solution to Park like A Boss</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Solving traffic problems with smart parking is the way forward, which is why parking adda is a need-based service in the country that looks at organising parking choices. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>We also attempt to make use of any available area that may be used efficiently through our&#39;rent your place&#39; and earn option. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>In order to provide a complete parking solution, we have created our own patented technology and produced our own equipment. If there are any problems that arise they can be resolve it in no time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p>ParkingAdda, in short, operates all of its technological operations and production processes in-house.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Vehicle owners will naturally reduce their use of illegal parking spots if they have access to better and safer parking facilities. As a consequence, a smart parking system may give facility owners with tools for better administration while also assisting in traffic congestion reduction.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p>As a result, our cities must act fast to implement an efficient smart parking programme. Additionally, local governments must educate car owners on the need of responsible and paid parking. After all, parking is a paid-for luxury rather than a right.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Also Read-</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>ParkingAdda - India ‘Park like a Boss’:</strong><br>\r\n </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Digital parking is one of the world&#39;s fastest growing and globally most extensively utilized Smart City Solutions. Universities, airports, public garages, and shopping malls are just a few of the organizations that have begun to see the significant benefits of automated/smart parking technology through the use of different Digital Parking applications. This current parking system is made feasible by the capacity to connect, analyze, and automate data received from gadgets, which is referred to as and driven by the Internet of Things. Read More</p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Why rent your Parking Space to Smart Parking Solutions like ParkingAdda?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Do you reside in the city center, close to many companies, commuting routes, or maybe the local Marriage grounds or Sports stadium, etc.? Someone is probably eager to pay you cash and park his car to save time and ensure vehicle safety. It may seem absurd, but depending on where you live, you might earn more than Rs. 15000 per month for renting out your parking place, or even more depending on the number of slots available. Yes, you read it correctly — Rs. 15000 per month for doing nothing. And, because it is passive income, you may continue to make money during off seasons even if you are travelling for work, occasion or on vacation. Read More</p>\r\n', 1, '19-10-22', '', 'parking'),
(4, '<h1><strong>How Drivers Will Benefit from Smart Parking?</strong></h1>\r\n', 'assets/uploads/How_Drivers_Will_Benefit_from_Smart_Parking.jpg', '<p>Smart Parking is now one of the most popular Smart City efforts, and India is no exception, with ParkingAdda introducing itself as a pioneer in Smart Parking projects. Soon searching for, ‘parking near me’ will be a norm.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Smart Parking, in a nutshell, is a parking system that can incorporate in-ground Smart Parking sensors, cameras, or counting sensors. These devices are often implanted in parking spaces or placed near them to detect whether parking bays are empty or filled. This is accomplished by the gathering of real-time data. The information is then transferred to a smart parking mobile app or website, which alerts users of the availability. Some businesses additionally provide in-app information such as parking fees and locations. This allows you to investigate every parking alternative available to you.</p>\r\n', '<p>Smart Parking is now one of the most popular Smart City efforts, and India is no exception, with ParkingAdda introducing itself as a pioneer in Smart Parking projects. Soon searching for, ‘parking near me’ will be a norm.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Smart Parking, in a nutshell, is a parking system that can incorporate in-ground Smart Parking sensors, cameras, or counting sensors. These devices are often implanted in parking spaces or placed near them to detect whether parking bays are empty or filled. This is accomplished by the gathering of real-time data. The information is then transferred to a smart parking mobile app or website, which alerts users of the availability. Some businesses additionally provide in-app information such as parking fees and locations. This allows you to investigate every parking alternative available to you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p>How it benefits?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Smart Parking is a low-barrier solution for communities that wish to leverage the potential of IOT to provide significant advantages to their residents since it is adaptable, scalable, and simple to implement. But why should politicians worry about Smart Parking, and why should they act now? It&#39;s because time isn&#39;t on our side. Allow us to clarify.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Within the passenger vehicle category, automobile sales increased to 1.21 lakh currently from 55,497 units, in June 2020. According to a Goldman Sachs study, India will become the world&#39;s third-largest auto market with 7.4 million cars.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Globally, by the end of 2016, the worldwide vehicle population was at 1.32 billion vehicles and trucks, according to Wards Intelligence. This figure is more than double what it was 20 years ago. Furthermore, car manufacturing and sales show no indications of slowing down. It is anticipated that by 2035, there will be almost 2 billion automobiles on the road, and others believe it may be even sooner. With such a rapid increase in car numbers yet such a restricted supply of space, the parking environment must adapt.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Below, we&#39;ll go over some of the key advantages that a smart parking system offers drivers. We&#39;ll discuss the benefits for cities in a subsequent piece.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Real Time Update-</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>A driver will receive Real-Time Updates of spot availability and bookings. He’ll receive reminders 15 Mins before parking time starts (in case of pre booked parking) and also 15 before the end time, giving an option to extent parking time via the app.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>There is less fuel waste- </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Drivers are guided to an open parking space which can be pre-booked, through a map guide. As a result, they waste less kilometers travelling in circles seeking for a parking place.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Spend less money- </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Obviously, if you drive more efficiently when looking for a parking spot, you will save gasoline. As a result, you will spend less money on gasoline. If you know your destination has a parking spot and you can book it in advance, it encourages a diver to drive a personal vehicle, rather than taking a cab service like Ola or Uber. Most of the time it works out cheaper.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Time is money-</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Furthermore, by travelling fewer kilometers in search of a parking spot, you will save important time that may be spent on work, recreation, or hobbies. As a result, you will spend less money on gasoline.          </p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Minimizing one&#39;s own environmental footprint-</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Another advantage of driving fewer kilometers to find a parking place is that you minimize individual pollution. Lower usage of all fossil fuels, gasoline, diesel, and the majority of alternative fuels emit emissions, particularly carbon dioxide (Co2). This pollutants will have no direct impact on human life. Co2 is, nevertheless, the most important contributor to greenhouse gases and, as a result, to climate change.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Increased security-</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Drivers are less distracted when looking for a parking spot because they know where they can park. They will be completely focused on the trip. By keeping their eyes on the road, they may reduce accidents and enhance safety for themselves, their own cars as well as other cars, and pedestrians.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Smart Parking eliminates the uncertainty of locating a parking place.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are not visiting a specific (region of a) city because you do not want to deal with the trouble of locating a parking place, ParkingAdda mobile app can help you with the same as you can choose and book an available spot in that location, up to 36 hours in advance. Knowing you&#39;ll be driving for a long time and will most likely end up somewhere far, far away from your destination might be disheartening.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Vehicle Safety-</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Smart parking with ParkingAdda will not guide you through a MAP exactly to your parking location, but also we have a dedicated representative at every spot for vehicle safety and additional guidance.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Smart parking will minimize the amount of time people spend looking for parking on the streets.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Smart parking like ParkingAdda will ensure that there are fewer automobiles on the streets that drive slowly and circle for a long time seeking for a parking place. This will improve traffic flow and minimize congestion in communities with a lack of parking space. Clear authorized parking spots will also reduce two side road parking issues, which is very common in areas like Mumbai. Our roadways are now congested, making traffic management difficult, and to make matters worse, around 30% of the roads have been occupied with double parking, i.e. parking on both sides of the road. As a result, there are fewer traffic bottlenecks, and drivers benefit from reduced traffic on the roads.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p>With a rise in the number of cars on the road and existing infrastructure difficulties, the demand for economies in mobility and parking becomes increasingly evident. Even if self-driving cars are becoming more common, the demand for parking does not appear to be reducing. At this point in time, cities must manage the possible effect of all future developments. This may be accomplished through accurate and future-proof design, as well as the use of a Smart Parking system to gather and analyze data, resulting in a healthier city.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Also Read-            </p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p>What are the benefits of renting your space to enhance smart parking?</p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Do you reside in the city center, close to many companies, commuting routes, or maybe the local Marriage grounds or Sports stadium, etc.? Someone is probably eager to pay you cash and park his car to save time and ensure vehicle safety. It may seem absurd, but depending on where you live, you might earn more than Rs. 15000 per month for renting out your parking place, or even more depending on the number of slots available. Yes, you read it correctly — Rs. 15000 per month for doing nothing. And, because it is passive income, you may continue to make money during off seasons even if you are travelling for work, occasion or on vacation. Read More</p>\r\n', 1, '19-10-22', '', 'parking'),
(5, '<h1><strong>Parking Issues in Mumbai</strong></h1>\r\n', 'assets/uploads/Parking_Issues_in_Mumbai.jpg', '<p>Its official, very soon Mumbaikars can book parking spaces in advance via the ‘ParkingAdda App’ within minutes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p>In India, parking spaces are getting increasingly scarce. Surely, we want to find parking spots quickly and in a much simpler way, rather than having to keep an eye out for our automobiles and going from one spot to the next in the hope of finding a parking. ParkingAdda is an internet service that assists you in finding a parking spot.</p>\r\n', '<p>Its official, very soon Mumbaikars can book parking spaces in advance via the ‘ParkingAdda App’ within minutes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p>In India, parking spaces are getting increasingly scarce. Surely, we want to find parking spots quickly and in a much simpler way, rather than having to keep an eye out for our automobiles and going from one spot to the next in the hope of finding a parking. ParkingAdda is an internet service that assists you in finding a parking spot.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p>We have tried and tested our proprietary technology through a pilot project in few areas within Mumbai, one can book a parking space as well as <strong>rent out your vacant parking space</strong> to ‘ParkingAdda’ easily via an online application.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p>“In a year every Mumbaikar spends around 11 days in a Traffic”.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p>In Mumbai, the Government Officials collects fines that are more than 1 lakh on a daily basis, do the math and you’ll get an idea on the number of vehicles parked in No Parking Zones. The major reasons or pain points of Vehicle driver and owners could be- lack of organized parking facilities or space, lack of parking guidance, etc. Even someone who has lived in Mumbai for a long time will find it difficult to obtain a suitable and secure parking space, as practically every Mumbaikar will attest with. Guess what, if you&#39;re new to a city like Mumbai, you’re most common and difficult struggle will be commuting owing to public transportation inconsistencies, massive traffic congestion, a lack of organized parking facilities, and expensive fines. Even worse, if your vehicle is towed, you&#39;ll have to figure out which tow site to contact, which will restart the vicious cycle from traffic to irregular public transport to fines and other procedures, etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>“Justice Kulkarni has addressed the subject of why unlawful parking is becoming a growing concern in terms of traffic management. In the same article, it was said that our highways are currently swamped with automobiles which makes traffic management difficult, and to top that about 30 percent of the roads have been filled by double parking, i.e. parking on both sides of the road. These are serious public concerns that must be addressed, and there is a need to develop long-term solutions so that we do not have a chaotic society.\" remarked Justice Kulkarni.”</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p>With ParkingAdda, one can save and plan their travel well by booking a parking spot online up to 36 hours in advance, instead of searching ‘Parking Near Me’ on the web - that doesn’t guarantee a spot, connecting with multiple friends and contacts to ask ‘Where can I find a safe/verified parking spot’ in a given location – which is time consuming. Surely, rather than doing what we do best, which is keeping an eye out for parking our cars and travelling from one area to the next, we want to discover parking spots quickly and easily, which is the USP of ‘ParkingAdda’.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>The main reason for traffic jams is unauthorized parking and solving parking issues will better traffic problems.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Illegal on-street parking is one of the key causes of bad traffic congestion in major city centers. Inadequate and poorly managed parking facilities frequently force drivers to park illegally on the streets. When such parking encroachments spill onto footpaths, they endanger pedestrians&#39; lives as well. Even the broadest roadways become congested owing to unauthorized parking. On the other side, some roads have more traffic than they can handle. Thus, road expansion is a fairly ad hoc solution to the problem.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Furthermore, with the lack of a centralized database, legislators and enforcers are uninformed about the traffic conditions and fail to take the necessary precautions to avoid traffic congestion. It&#39;s not difficult to picture that inadequate traffic management is the cause of traffic congestions. Even while local governments strive for forethought when planning and building a township, amenities such as paid parking are frequently overlooked. Furthermore, they may underestimate or act as if they have underestimated the vehicular density on specific roadways. Inadequate consideration of such critical elements contributes to traffic congestion in the long run.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Solving traffic issues with smart parking the way forward and this is the reasons that make ParkingAdda a need based service in the country, which looks at organizing parking options. Through our <strong>‘rent your spot’</strong> and earn option we also try and make use of every vacant space that can be used efficiently. We have developed our very own proprietary technology and also manufacture our own equipment’s in order to provide a full proof parking solution. Any issues faced if any can be rectified quickly.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In short <strong>ParkingAdda</strong> manages all its technical operations and manufacturing processes in house.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p>When vehicle owners have access to improved and safer parking facilities, they will naturally minimize their usage of unlawful places. As a result, a smart parking system can provide facility owners with tools for better administration while also helping to reduce traffic congestion.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p>As a result, our cities should move quickly to establish an effective smart parking scheme. Furthermore, city governments must educate vehicle owners on the value of responsible and paid parking. After all, parking is a privilege that must be paid for rather than a right.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Also Read-</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>How Drivers Will Benefit from Smart Parking?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Digital parking is one of the world&#39;s fastest growing and globally most extensively utilized Smart City Solutions. Universities, airports, public garages, and shopping malls are just a few of the organizations that have begun to see the significant benefits of automated/smart parking technology through the use of different Digital Parking applications. This current parking system is made feasible by the capacity to connect, analyze, and automate data received from gadgets, which is referred to as and driven by the Internet of Things…Read More</p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Markets for best ‘Diwali Shopping’ Deals, in Mumbai.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Better known as Bombay, Mumbai is renowned as \"the city of dreams,\" and it is embellished with countless cultural riches, a rich history, and a golden past that never disappoints a traveler. Mumbai, the city of visionaries, artists, connoisseurs, and fashionistas, has its own claim to fame and attractiveness. Despite being one of the busiest cities in the world, Mumbai has an allure that entices you to put it in your vacation itinerary.</p>\r\n', 1, '19-10-22', '', 'parking');
