(6, '<h1><strong>Parking Management is a Need Based Solution in India.</strong></h1>\r\n', 'assets/uploads/Parking_Management_is_a_Need_Based_Solution_in_India.jpg', '<p>It’s official: Mumbaikars will soon be able to reserve parking spots in advance using the &#39;ParkingAdda App&#39; in just a few seconds.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Free parking has become a severe urban planning and public health concern in a country where it took 60 years to acquire 100 million automobiles but only ten years to add another 100 million. When people complain that \"it&#39;s so difficult to find parking places these days\" or that they are caught in never-ending traffic jams, major part of the issue is irregular parking.</p>\r\n', '<p>It’s official: Mumbaikars will soon be able to reserve parking spots in advance using the &#39;ParkingAdda App&#39; in just a few seconds.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Free parking has become a severe urban planning and public health concern in a country where it took 60 years to acquire 100 million automobiles but only ten years to add another 100 million. When people complain that \"it&#39;s so difficult to find parking places these days\" or that they are caught in never-ending traffic jams, major part of the issue is irregular parking.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Parking places are becoming increasingly rare in India. We all want to find parking places quickly and easily, rather than having to keep an eye out of our cars and driving from one location to the next in the hopes of finding one. &#39;ParkingAdda&#39; is an online parking service that helps you locate a parking place easily online.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Car owner’s demand free or low-cost parking wherever they go, and any attempt to charge them a fee is met with derision, resulting in a rash of haphazard parking that not only obstructs pedestrian movement but also causes serious traffic congestion a significant waste of time and a serious public health issue given the harmful effects of vehicular pollution.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Parking has become a big challenge for commuters as the population and number of automobiles on the road has grown. While road extension, metro construction, and cab aggregators are being used to alleviate traffic congestion, the underlying problem of uncontrolled parking remains a serious concern.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As a result, mobility as a service has emerged, which uses AI and IoT to record and anticipate mobility data. Smart online parking applications have integrated this new technology, allowing for more efficient parking management.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p>In India&#39;s top eight cities, there are around 600K paid parking places distributed between residential, work, shopping, airports, railways, hospitals, and leisure. On-street, open air, floors of stores and offices, residential and work private property are all part of these examples of parking spaces.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Here are a few brief statistics on current world challenges that will astound you:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n <li>A Delhi commuter spends more than 80 hours a year looking for a parking spot, and the situation is similar in other metro areas like as Mumbai.</li>\r\n <li>Each year, drivers in the United States spend $20.4 billion and 44 hours looking for parking.</li>\r\n <li>Drivers in the United Kingdom spend $6.7 billion and spend 17 hours looking for parking.</li>\r\n <li>Every year, German drivers spend 4.4 billion euros and 44 hours looking for parking.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The digital parking system from ParkingAdda uses real-time data, apps, and accurate sensors to show users which parking spaces are available and which are not. The idea is to cut down on time spent physically looking for a suitable parking lot, space, or even floor. Some systems may offer a comprehensive set of services, including parking time notifications, online payments, and even car-finding capabilities for larger parking lots. Both lot owners and customers can gain substantially from an automated parking system. The following are some of the most notable advantages:</p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p>1. Parking optimization: Users can use the app to discover the best available parking spot, saving them time, effort, and money. The parking lot soon fills up, and businesses and commercial organizations can take advantage of the available space. Unauthorized parking and on-street parking can both be reduced.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. Improved Traffic Flow: As fewer cars are required to go about looking for an open parking spot, traffic flow improves. Automated legal online parking solutions will reduction in the number of on-street parked vehicles, which is the most important reason behind traffic congestions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. Pollution Reduction: Looking for a parking spot uses far too much automobile oil, petrol, gasoline, diesel, CNG, and other fuels in a single day. An ideal parking solution will greatly reduce travel time while also reducing the amount of daily car exhaust and, as a result, India&#39;s and the world&#39;s pollution.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4. Better User Experience: An online parking solution will bring together all components of the user experience into a single action. The destination arrival procedure easily integrates driver payment, location search, time notifications, and site identification.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>5. Additional Revenue Streams: Individuals, organizations, and other institutions can generate a passive income by renting out their premises.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>6. Simple Integrated Payments: The &#39;ParkingAdda&#39; application collects and distributes invoicing and payments. This could also help the organization maintain account transparency between customers and vendors.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>7. Increased Employment Costs: Several additional revenue sources is a potential with this smart parking system. For example, we would have parking lot representatives, which would increase employment in India during these times of job scarcity.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>8. Improved Car Security: Our spot representative and vehicle have real-time parking lot data, which may help avoid suspicious behavior and parking violations. Furthermore, if there was less spot-searching traffic on the highways, accidents caused by the obstruction of hunting for parking might be reduced. These parking guides will also facilitate parked vehicle safety, which is also a concern in India. Scratches, dents, tire inflations, etc. are a few common vehicle safety issues faced.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>9. Safety and Security of the Space: ParkingAdda does give Individuals, organizations, and other institutions an option to rent their spaces and earn additional income. Users can only utilize our parking places for registered vehicles, and our spot representative will be on site to recognize any suspicious conduct, parking offences, etc. and ensure space safety.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p>As evidence of the aforementioned advantages, any organization or government would surely benefit from the usage of a digital online parking solution such as the &#39;ParkingAdda&#39;. Individuals are still unable to locate a parking space in some of the world&#39;s largest cities, where there are approximately four parking spaces per car. In India is said that the number of cars exceed the number of available parking spots. As the world&#39;s population grows and gets more sophisticated, it&#39;s more important than ever to put in place a user-friendly and well-planned parking system that can be used anywhere. In India, ParkingAdda is a need-based solution for the benefit of all citizens as well as the environment as a whole.</p>\r\n', 1, '19-10-22', '', 'parking'),
